BILLION DECREASE IN NET CASH PROCEEDS FROM ISSUANCE AND REPAYMENTS OF SHORT-TERM AND LONG-TERM DEBT. FINANCING ACTIVITIES ALSO INCLUDED A $1.9 BILLION INCREASE IN CASH USED FOR COMMON STOCK

REPURCHASES, WHICH WAS OFFSET IN PART BY A $1.7 BILLION INCREASE IN CASH RECEIVED FROM COMMON STOCK ISSUED. CASH USED FOR INVESTING DECREASED $4.5 BILLION DUE TO A $3.3 BILLION DECREASE IN CASH USED FOR COMBINED INVESTMENT PURCHASES, SALES, AND

